args.code:
import pandas as pd

df = pd.read_csv('source_files/Adult.csv')

df['income'] = df['income'].apply(lambda x: 1 if x == '>50K' else 0)

df['gender'] = df['sex'].apply(lambda x: 1 if x == 'Male' else 0)

# Calculate probabilities
prob_high_income_protected = df[df['gender'] == 1]['income'].mean()
prob_high_income_non_protected = df[df['gender'] == 0]['income'].mean()

# Compute Risk Difference
risk_diff = prob_high_income_protected - prob_high_income_non_protected

print('Risk Difference:', risk_diff)
